<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
	<!--
	2026-06-03 — DD Mau iOS entitlements file.

	Why this exists:
	  The wrapped iOS app needs the aps-environment entitlement to call
	  UIApplication.registerForRemoteNotifications(). Without it, iOS
	  throws NSInternalInconsistencyException at the FIRST call from the
	  @capacitor-firebase/messaging plugin's native init - and that
	  exception terminates the WKWebView process before any of our
	  JavaScript can run. Result: white-screen-after-PIN with nothing
	  visible in Safari Web Inspector (the WebContent died too early to
	  hook).

	  We chased this as a JS bug for hours on 2026-06-02. The real fix
	  is two lines: this entitlement key + the matching Xcode capability.

	State right now:
	  This FILE exists, but is NOT yet referenced by ios/App/App.xcodeproj/
	  project.pbxproj. That's intentional - referencing it from pbxproj
	  without also having the matching capability + provisioning profile
	  configured would break code signing on the next Xcode build, and
	  we promised "don't break anything" overnight.

	  To activate this entitlement, Andrew clicks "+ Capability" in
	  Xcode -> Signing & Capabilities and adds "Push Notifications".
	  Xcode auto-links this file (or recreates it identically) and
	  registers CODE_SIGN_ENTITLEMENTS in the build settings. After
	  that the next Xcode build signs with aps-environment and the
	  FCM plugin can register for remote notifications without
	  crashing the WebView.

	  Full step-by-step instructions in FCM_RUNBOOK.md at repo root.

	Why "development" not "production":
	  aps-environment values: development (sandbox APNs - TestFlight +
	  local Xcode builds), production (real APNs - App Store).
	  Xcode auto-flips this at archive time based on the build
	  configuration: Debug -> development, Release -> production.
	  Hardcoding "development" here makes local Xcode builds work; the
	  archive step still produces a Release build with production set
	  automatically. No manual flip needed at submission time.
	-->
	<key>aps-environment</key>
	<string>development</string>
</dict>
</plist>
